<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 1:25PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Roanoke, the City
of Salem, and the City of Roanoke through 200 PM EDT...
At 121 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms with very heavy rainfall between Poages Mill, Salem,
and Roanoke. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Urban flooding with this area of thunderstorms is likely.
Underpasses, low-lying, and normally flood-prone areas will
be the most impacted.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Catawba...
Bent Mountain...
Glenvar...
and Hollins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
